4. DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) in Data Engineering
A DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) is a key concept in workflow orchestration, especially in tools like Apache Airflow. It represents a series of tasks that must be executed in a specific order, ensuring that no cycles (infinite loops) exist.

5. ğŸ”¹ What is a DAG?
âœ… Directed â†’ Tasks have a clear sequence (A â†’ B â†’ C)
âœ… Acyclic â†’ No task loops back to an earlier task (No A â†’ B â†’ A)
âœ… Graph â†’ A structure of nodes (tasks) and edges (dependencies)

6. ğŸš€ Why Use DAGs in Workflow Orchestration?
âœ… Manages Dependencies â†’ Ensures tasks run in the right order
âœ… Prevents Infinite Loops â†’ No cycles mean no infinite execution
âœ… Enables Parallel Execution â†’ Some tasks can run at the same time
âœ… Easily Scalable â†’ Modify and extend workflows dynamically
